 :tx/rationale "Create task: FT-PGO: Implement PGO (Profile-Guided Optimization) loop — refine coupling weights from F(T) outcomes (ADR-TOPOLOGY-004, INV-TOPOLOGY-016). BACKGROUND: The PGO loop closes the self-improvement cycle. After each topology harvest: (1) Compare predicted coupling (from plan) with observed coupling (from actual conflict data). (2) Compute prediction_delta = |predicted - observed| per task pair. (3) Update coupling weights toward observed values using exponential moving average: w_new = alpha * w_observed + (1-alpha) * w_old, alpha = 0.3. (4) Store updated weights as :topology/coupling-weights datom. (5) INV-TOPOLOGY-016: prediction error decreases monotonically after warmup (>= 3 sessions). The historical coupling dimension (w_h) is populated by the PGO loop: past conflicts between task pairs create historical coupling for future topology plans. APPROACH: (1) PgoResult struct with: prediction_delta, weight_updates, historical_conflicts. (2) run_pgo(store, plan: &TopologyPlan, actual_ft: &TopologyFitness) -> PgoResult. (3) pgo_to_datoms(result) -> Vec<Datom>. (4) Update :topology/coupling-weights. (5) Record :topology/historical-conflict for each observed conflict pair. ACCEPTANCE: (A) After 3+ sessions with PGO, mean prediction_delta decreases. (B) Historical coupling for past-conflicting pairs is > 0 in next plan. (C) Weight updates bounded: no single update changes any weight by > 0.1. DEPENDS-ON: t-072d762f (FT-COMPUTE), t-b7d04e92 (TOPO-COMPOSITE). FILE: crates/braid-kernel/src/topology.rs"
